SYNOPSIS
========
   int strstr(string str, string str2         )
   int strstr(string str, string str2, int pos)

DESCRIPTION
===========
Returns the index of <str2> in <str>, searching from position <pos> on.

The returned index is relative to the beginning of the string. If <str2> is
not found in <str>, -1 is returned.

If <pos> is negative, it designates the start position relative to the end of
the string (the search will still proceed towards the end of the string).

   See Also:
      strrstr(E), strlen(E), sscanf(E), sprintf(E), explode(E)
